Maintenance:  The maintenance program at the Facility is intended to preserve the mechanical integrity of the process equipment to minimize the potential for an accidental release. The maintenance program includes equipment inspection, preventative maintenance, record keeping, and training. The latest equipment inspections were conducted in June 2018. The most recent review of maintenance procedures was conducted in June 2018.



RMP Change Management:  Operation, safety, and environmental issues must be reviewed prior to initiation of a process change to ensure that they do not compromise the operational safety and integrity of the Anhydrous Ammonia Process, and to minimize adverse effects to worker safety and public health. The Facility RMP Management of Change (RMP MOC) procedures are used to evaluate changes to process materials, controls, equipment, and procedures.



Pre-startup Review:  The pre-startup review applies to additions or modifications to the Anhydrous Ammonia Process that require the safety information to be revised or updated. Whenever changes in affected processes are identified or planned, they must be evaluated as to the need for a pre-startup safety review. This assessment is undertaken in conjunction with the RMP MOC review. Additionally, a pre-startup safety review is performed in conjunction with the RMP MOC review when the proposed change requires modifications to the safety procedures.



